          <from>MR. MAT WHYNOTT</from>
          <p>MR. MAT WHYNOTT : Mr. Speaker, I'm going to speak in support of this bill as well. It gives me an opportunity to stand and talk a little bit about the importance of this industry to Nova Scotia. Again, as I said, I speak in favour of Bill No. 119 moving forward to the Law Amendments Committee.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : If I recognize the minister it will be to close the debate.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#dec41d7a-1f3f-40db-bdc4-d55134cb9a68">
          <from>HON. MARILYN MORE</from>
          <p>HON. MARILYN MORE : Mr. Speaker, I want to thank all honourable members for their comments and support. I move second reading of Bill No. 119.</p>
        </speech>
